@startuml event_flow_diagram

title BTG Desafio - Fluxo de Eventos RabbitMQ (Sequência Completa)

actor Cliente

participant "API Gateway\n:8082" as gateway
participant "Customer Service\n(ms-customer)" as customer
participant "customer.exchange\n[TopicExchange]" as c_exchange
participant "customer.queue.created\n[durable]" as c_created_q
participant "customer.queue.deleted\n[durable]" as c_deleted_q
participant "Order Service\n(ms-order)" as order
participant "order.exchange\n[TopicExchange]" as o_exchange
participant "order.queue.created\n[durable]" as o_created_q
participant "order.queue.deleted\n[durable]" as o_deleted_q

== Criar Cliente ==

Cliente -> gateway : POST /api/v1/customer
gateway -> customer : POST /api/v1/customer
customer -> c_exchange : publica CustomerCreatedEvent\n(routing key: customer.created)
customer --> gateway : 202 Accepted
c_exchange -> c_created_q : binding customer.created
c_created_q -> customer : @RabbitListener\nhandleCustomerCreated(CustomerCreatedEvent)
customer -> customer : customerService.createCustomer()\n→ persiste Customer no MySQL

== Remover Cliente ==

Cliente -> gateway : DELETE /api/v1/customer/{id}
gateway -> customer : DELETE /api/v1/customer/{id}
customer -> c_exchange : publica DefaultEvent(id)\n(routing key: customer.deleted)
customer --> gateway : 202 Accepted
c_exchange -> c_deleted_q : binding customer.deleted
c_deleted_q -> customer : @RabbitListener\nhandleCustomerDeleted(DefaultEvent)
customer -> order : [OpenFeign] DELETE /api/v1/order/customer/{id}
note right of order : Remove todos os pedidos\ne itens do cliente
customer -> customer : customerService.deleteCustomer()\n→ remove Customer do MySQL

== Criar Pedido ==

Cliente -> gateway : POST /api/v1/order
gateway -> order : POST /api/v1/order
order -> o_exchange : publica OrderEvent\n(routing key: order.created)
order --> gateway : 202 Accepted
o_exchange -> o_created_q : binding order.created
o_created_q -> order : @RabbitListener\nhandle(OrderEvent)
order -> order : orderService.createOrder()\n→ persiste Order + OrderItems no MySQL

== Remover Pedido ==

Cliente -> gateway : DELETE /api/v1/order/{id}
gateway -> order : DELETE /api/v1/order/{id}
order -> o_exchange : publica DefaultEvent(id)\n(routing key: order.deleted)
order --> gateway : 204 No Content
o_exchange -> o_deleted_q : binding order.deleted
o_deleted_q -> order : @RabbitListener\nhandleOrderDeleted(DefaultEvent)
order -> order : orderService.deleteOrder()\n→ remove Order + OrderItems do MySQL

note right of gateway
    Padrão assíncrono (event sourcing leve):
    Controller publica o evento e retorna imediatamente.
    Persistência ocorre de forma assíncrona via @RabbitListener.
    Eventos: customer.created, customer.deleted,
             order.created, order.deleted
end note

@enduml